# Presentation Layer — Coding Standards

Inherits all design system guidelines from the root `app/.cursorrules`.

This file focuses on **code conventions** for the presentation layer.

## Naming Conventions

| Element                        | Style                        | Example                    |
|--------------------------------|------------------------------|----------------------------|
| Classes, enums, typedefs       | `UpperCamelCase`             | `BarListItem`, `FilterMode`|
| Extensions                     | `UpperCamelCase`             | `StringExtension`          |
| Files and directories          | `lowercase_with_underscores` | `bar_list_item.dart`       |
| Variables, functions, params   | `lowerCamelCase`             | `isHappyHourActive`        |
| Constants                      | `lowerCamelCase`             | `defaultPadding`           |
| Acronyms (3+ letters)          | Capitalize like words        | `HttpRequest`, `barId`     |

## Code Patterns

### Widget Structure

```dart
class BarListItem extends StatelessWidget {
  final Bar bar;           // Required params first
  final VoidCallback? onTap;  // Optional params after

  const BarListItem({
    super.key,
    required this.bar,
    this.onTap,
  });

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final theme = Theme.of(context);  // Access theme first
    final l10n = AppLocalizations.of(context);  // Then localization

    return /* widget tree */;
  }
}
```

### Avoid

- ❌ Leading underscores for non-private members
- ❌ Hungarian notation (`kValue`, `mVariable`, `sInstance`)
- ❌ Explicit library names
- ❌ `SCREAMING_CAPS` for constants
- ❌ Unused callback parameters (use `_` wildcard)

### Prefer

- ✅ `const` constructors where possible
- ✅ Expression bodies for single-return methods
- ✅ `final` for immutable local variables
- ✅ Null-aware operators (`?.`, `??`, `??=`)
- ✅ Collection literals over constructors
